awards.title: Dean's List
awards.summary: Undergraduate students are awarded the Dean’s List distinction if they: (1) earn a semester grade point average of 3.5 or higher based on 12 credits or more taken for a grade (C/NC courses do not count), and (2) do not receive grades of W, I, F, or NC for that semester.

awards.title: Academic Honors
awards.summary: Awarded to students that graduate with a cumulative GPA of 3.0 or above and completed 4 credits of math, 4 credits of science, and 2 credits from AP/IB/Running Start courses.

awards.title: CTE Honors
awards.summary: Awarded to students that graduate with a cumulative GPA of 3.0 or above and completed a two-course sequence in an approved CTE program or program of study with a B or better and met or exceeded proficiency on a performance-based assessment.
